- $\answer{\left[-\dfrac{\pi}{2}, \dfrac{\pi}{2}\right]}$
- If we solve the equation $|x^2\arcsin(x)| = 0.5$ for $x$, we have

  $$
  \begin{aligned}
  \hspace{9.4em} x^2\arcsin(x) &= \pm 0.5 \\[6pt]
  x &= \pm 0.761 \hspace{3em} [\text{by using G.D.C.}]\end{aligned}
  $$

  Hence we get

  $$
  \begin{aligned}

  \begin{array}{rclcrcl}
  -\dfrac{\pi}{2} \leq x^2\arcsin(x) &<& -0.5 \hspace{0.5em}\,&\text{ or }\hspace{0.5em}\,& 0.5 &<& x^2\arcsin(x) \leq \dfrac{\pi}{2} \\[9pt]
  -1 \leq x &<& -0.761 \hspace{0.5em}\,&\text{ or }\hspace{0.5em}\,& 0.761 &<& x \leq 1 \\
  \end{array} \hspace{0.9em}\end{aligned}
  $$

  Hence the set of solutions
to the inequality $|x^2\arcsin(x)| > 0.5$ is

  $$
  \begin{aligned}
  \answer{[-1,-0.761)\cup(0.761,1]}\end{aligned}
  $$
